    "Title": "DEAD SAINTS -- ~mission(ReputationRank) Rank, ~mission(CargoGradeToken) Scale Cargo Run",
    "DisplayTitle": "DEAD SAINTS -- Rookie Rank, Small Scale Cargo Run",
    "Description": "Got an interesting one. Some folks who were suckered into life/labor contracts with Hurston Dynamics want to get as far from Lorville as they possibly can. They struck a deal with a people mover and got themselves put on ice. Now they just need someone to pick them up and give them a ride. \n\nIf you're up for some popsicle smuggling, you'll find ~mission(total) cryopods at <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4> that need to go to <EM4>~mission(Destination|Address)</EM4>. Make sure you have space in your cargo hold for size <EM4>~mission(MissionMaxSCUSize)</EM4> containers. If you use a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4>, you should be able to get everyone loaded up before Hurston security catches on. \n\nHD isn't too keen on anyone slipping out of their contracts, so watch your back. They shoot to kill. \n\nIf you can pull this off, there's a nice paycheck in it for you.\n\n-Twitch",
    "DisplayDescription": "Got an interesting one. Some folks who were suckered into life/labor contracts with Hurston Dynamics want to get as far from Lorville as they possibly can. They struck a deal with a people mover and got themselves put on ice. Now they just need someone to pick them up and give them a ride. \n\nIf you're up for some popsicle smuggling, you'll find [total] cryopods at <EM4>Teasa Spaceport</EM4> that need to go to <EM4>[Destination|Address]</EM4>. Make sure you have space in your cargo hold for size <EM4>2 SCU</EM4> containers. If you use a <EM4>handheld tractor beam</EM4>, you should be able to get everyone loaded up before Hurston security catches on. \n\nHD isn't too keen on anyone slipping out of their contracts, so watch your back. They shoot to kill. \n\nIf you can pull this off, there's a nice paycheck in it for you.\n\n-Twitch",
